$env:PATH += ";D:\shell\shell-javascript\externalPrograms"
this command adds the externalPrograms to the system environment

dir "C:\Windows\System32" | where {$_.Extension -eq ".exe"}
this command lists all the .exe files in the System32 directory, 
which are the executable programs available in the system.

echo $env:PATH?
this command displays the current value of the PATH environment variable TO 
verify that the externalPrograms directory has been added successfully.

